<title>POLAND: WARSAW BOURSE CLEARS KGHM SHARES FOR TRADE.</title>
<headline>WARSAW BOURSE CLEARS KGHM SHARES FOR TRADE.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1997-06-11</dateline>
<text>
<p>The supervisory board of the Warsaw Stock Exchage cleared shares in Polish copper concern KGHM Polska Miedz SA for trade on the bourse's main market, the bourse said in a statement on Wednesday.</p>
<p>Poland is offering up to 36 percent or 72 million shares of KGHM in a public offering starting on June 30. The offer was priced at 15-23 zlotys per share.</p>
<p>The privatisation plan also assumes that, up to 15 percent of KGHM would be set aside for about 50,000 present and former employees, leaving the state treasury with 49 percent.</p>
<p>-- Warsaw Newsroom +48 22 653 9700</p>
